title: Maximum height of a trajectory
prompt: The graph below shows the relationship between height and rocket flight. Describe how the rocket's height is changing between 7 and 11 seconds.
hint: Describe the behavior of the graph between these values of t.
feedback: To compare the relationship of the rocket's height over some time interval, observe the direction the graph is going during that time interval. For the time period of 7 to 11 seconds in this graph, the rocket's height is decreasing as time goes by. At 7 seconds, the rocket is approximately 230 meters high. At 11 seconds, the rocket is approximate 20 meters high.
